This problem requires a complete understanding of the modulo operator and the concept of array length.

The problem is asking to find the minimum length of an array after performing some operations on it. The operations are as follows:
- Select two distinct indices i and j from nums, such that nums[i] > 0 and nums[j] > 0.
- Insert the result of nums[i] % nums[j] at the end of nums.
- Delete the elements at indices i and j from nums.
The objective is to minimize the length of the array.

