The reason is that when a node needs to be deleted from a linked list, the previous node needs to be pointed to the next node of the node that needs to be deleted. This is done by changing the "next" pointer of the previous node to the "next" pointer of the node that needs to be deleted.

In the case of removing the current node, we do not need to change the "next" pointer of the previous node, as we can simply skip it by moving the "cur" pointer to the next node. This is achieved by setting cur.next = cur.next.next;.

